A population of wild wood bison were successfully reintroduced to the plains of Alaska for the first time in over a century .
The moment was captured on video and shows Alaska Department of Fish and Game Biologist Tom Seaton leading 100 wood b b to freedom on a snowmobile .
The land mammals were freed from a temporary pen , where they had been kept for just over a week during the transition .
